---
Source:
  Title: A Year with Rumi
  Translator: Coleman Barks
  Author: Rumi
  ISBN: 978-0060845971
  Publisher: HarperOne
Format: Verse
By: Rumi
Title: Red
Description: February 26
---
Red with shyness, the red
that became all the rosegarden reds.

The red distance,
red of the stove boiling water,
red of the mountain turning bloodred,
a mountain holding rubies secretly inside.

Do I love more you
or your modesty?
